This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image captioning and enhancing the generative capability of machines based on visual features. It also involves the use of regional image features, which is a common topic in the computer vision field. 

It could also belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-category as it deals with improving the quality of captions generated by machines. 

The paper also involves the use of tensors and learning interactions, which are common topics in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

Finally, it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it deals with combining visual and textual information to generate captions for images.
